trans-unit.source: Management of the graphics devices, contexts, image and texture objects is up to the application. The device or context that will be used by Qt Quick must be created before calling initialize(). The creation of the the texture object can be deferred, see below. Qt 5.4 introduces the ability for QOpenGLContext to adopt existing native contexts. Together with QQuickRenderControl this makes it possible to create a QOpenGLContext that shares with an external rendering engine's existing context. This new QOpenGLContext can then be used to render the Qt Quick scene into a texture that is accessible by the other engine's context too. trans-unit.source: Managing heap allocated objects manually is hard and error prone, with the common result that code leaks memory and is hard to maintain. QScopedPointer is a small utility class that heavily simplifies this by assigning stack-based memory ownership to heap allocations, more generally called resource acquisition is initialization(RAII).
trans-unit.target: 手动管理分配给堆的对象非常困难且容易出错，其常见的结果是代码会泄漏内存并且难以维护。QScopedPointer是一个小型实用程序类，它通过将基于堆栈的内存所有权分配给堆分配来大大简化此过程，通常将其称为资源获取即初始化（RAII）。

trans-unit.source: Menus in Qt are implemented in QMenu. The QMenu keeps a list of actions, which it draws as menu items. When QMenu receives paint events, it calculates the size of each menu item and draws them individually with CE_MenuItem. Menu items do not have a separate element for their label (contents), so all drawing is done in CE_MenuItem. The menu also draws the frame of the menu with PE_FrameMenu. It also draws CE_MenuScroller if the style supports scrolling. CE_MenuTearOff is drawn if the menu is too large for its bounding rectangle.
trans-unit.target: Qt中的菜单在QMenu中实现。该QMenu保持的动作列表，它汲取营养菜单项。当QMenu接收绘制事件时，它将计算每个菜单项的大小，并使用 CE_MenuItem 分别绘制它们。菜单项的标签（内容）没有单独的元素，因此所有绘制都在 CE_MenuItem 中完成。菜单还使用 PE_FrameMenu 绘制菜单的框架。如果样式支持滚动，则还将绘制 CE_MenuScroller 。如果菜单对于其边界矩形而言太大，则会绘制 CE_MenuTearOff 。
